anatomy of the little ant.

334
00:14:57,120 --> 00:15:00,720
<i>The body of the ant is divided</i>
<i>into three sections:</i>

335
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:04,600
<i>The head, the thorax</i>
<i>and the abdomen.</i>

336
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,440
<i>They're enclosed in a hard,</i>

337
00:15:06,560 --> 00:15:09,800
<i>armor-like covering</i>
<i>called the exoskeleton,</i>

338
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,480
<i>which provides some protection</i>

339
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,680
<i>from other nasty little</i>
<i>insects.</i>

340
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:15,480
<i>But unfortunately,</i>

341
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,160
<i>not from the dissector's</i>
<i>scalpel.</i>

342
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:20,240
<i>See, nothing to it.</i>

343
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:21,800
<i>He's not such a toughie.</i>

344
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:23,520
<i>And his legs,</i>
<i>they help him carry</i>

345
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,200
<i>hundreds of times</i>
<i>his own weight,</i>

346
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,640
<i>but look at this:</i>

347
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:29,320
<i>You're not so strong</i>
<i>compared to me.</i>

348
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,920
<i>Four, five, six. Ha!</i>

349
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:34,760
I didn't know ants
had six legs, Marcus.

